# GitHub Issue Title Format Rule

When creating GitHub issues, always use conventional commit format for titles:

**Format**: `type(scope): description`

**Examples**:
- `feat(api): Add Gemini 2.0 Flash Live API support for real-time speech translation`
- `feat(extension): Add Microsoft Edge browser compatibility and Edge Add-ons store support`
- `fix(audio): Resolve virtual device cleanup on application exit`
- `docs(readme): Update installation instructions for Linux`
- `refactor(ui): Improve settings panel component structure`

**Types**:
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks
- `perf`: Performance improvements
- `ci`: CI/CD changes

**Scope**: Specify the area of codebase affected (api, ui, extension, audio, etc.)

**Description**: Clear, concise description in lowercase, no period at end